The reason this appears as part of Trebino is due to the fact that towns in Macedonia are at the moment represented as nodes instead of areas. In this case the Nominatim algorithm reacts on proximity, and this street is closer to Trebino town-node than to Makedonski Brod town-node.  One solution is to use the 'is_in' tag on all streets in the north of Makedonski Brod, but is not the best solution. The real solution is to map the towns (in this case at least Trebino) with its corresponding boundaries.  The information of the town limits are in the Cadastre and at this point I don't know if this information is free to be used or not.  A better implementation would be to get the boundaries of all towns as vector and import them/map them into OSM.  For the moment just closing this note and waiting until all that can be implemented.
